      • popStack

        public Stack<T> popStack​(int count)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Deletes and returns the required number of elements from the stack. The order of the elements is the same as in the original stack.
        Parameters:
        count - Number of top stack elements to be thrown out of the stack
        Returns:
        A stack consisting of count of the top elements of the stack. The order of the elements in the stack is the same as in the original
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if count is negative or there are not enough elements in the stack
